------what is property in CSS?

1) That use for the style the HTML elements 
2) Each HTML element can be styled using different CSS Properties

3) There are many CSS properties to style the elements of HTML
		color
		size
		border
		text

----------How to add a property in CSS?

	** A CSS property consists of a property 
		name and a property value.

	** To specify more than one of a property,
		each pair is separated by a semicolon 


----------Text properties of CSS
	

	** Let's see how we can change the text 
		using CSS properties 

	** Text properties discussed,
		* Font Family 
		* Font size 
		* Font weight 



-------------Text properties 


	** Font-family 
		* Allow us to change the font type used 
		* any standard font can be used.

	** Font-size
		* May be specified using a few different types.
		* Easiest to work with is pixels (px).

	** Font_size
		* May be specified using a few different types.
		* Easiest to work with is pixels (px).




------------Colour properties of CSS

	** Let's see how we can change the color 
		using CSS properties 

	** Color Properties discussed,
		* color
		* background color



-----------Colour properties 

	** Color
		* Allows us to specify the color of the text.

	** Background-color
		* Allows us to specify the background color for 
			the element.



-------------Spacing properties of CSS
	
	** Let's see how we can change the 
		spacing using CSS properties.

	** Spacing properties discussed,
		* padding
		* margin
		* border



--------------Spacing properties-padding

	** Padding 
		* Refers to the space around out content

	** Margin 
		* Similar to padding in that is affects the spacing
			around the content.

	** Border
		* Is in between the padding and margin.


------------------------What we learnt -------------

	1- CSS property is used to style the HTML elements
	2- Main CSS properties can be categorized into 
		text, color and spacing 
	3- How CSS properties can be used to change the look and feel
		of the HTML content.



##-----------------------------------------------------------------------------##

	3.3  CSS Background styling ----------------


	CSS Backgrounds 

		** CSS background property is used to define the 
			background effects on HTML elements.

		** CSS background properties :
			* Background-color
			* Background-image 
			* Background-repeat
			* Background-attachment
			* Background-position

	CSS background-color

		** used to specify the background color of the element.
		** colors can be specified by,

			* valid color name - eg:"blue"
			* hex value - eg: #00ff00
			* RGB value - eg: rgb(255,0,0)


		<style>
		body{
			background-color: blue;
		}
		h1{
			background-color: #00ff00; // Green color-hex value 
		}
		p{
			background-color: rgb(255, 0, 0); // Red color-RGB value
		}

		</style>



		CSS background-image 

			** Used to set an image as a background of an element 
				<style>
					body {
						background-image: url('gradient.jpg');
					}

				</style>


		CSS background-repeat 

			** By default, background-image property repeats the 
				image in both horizontally and vertically.

			** Can control the repeating property.
				* If repeat horizontally only :
					
					<style>
						body {
							background-image: url('gradient.jpg');
							background-repeat: repeat-x;
						}

					</style>

			** Can control the repeating property.
				* if repeat vertically only:
				
					<style>
						body {
							background-image:url('gradient.png');
							background-repeat: repeat-y;
						}
					</style>


			** Can control the repeating property.
				* if no repeat:

					<style>
						body {
							background-image: url('gradient.png');
							background-repeat: no-repeat;
						}
					</style>


		CSS background-position

			** Background image can be positioned.

				<style>
					body {
						background-image: url('tree.png');
						background-repeat: no-repeat;
						background-position: right;
					}
				</style>

				(top, bottom, corner, left, right)



		CSS background-attachment

				** Specifies whether the background image should scroll
					or be fixed.

				<style>
					body {
					background-image: url('tree.png');
					background-repeat: no-repeat;
					background-position: right;
					background-image: fixed;
					}

				</style>


				What we learnt 
					## CSS Background property
					## Background effects on HTML elements

